<subSubSection pageId="248" pageNumber="526" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="248.[2068,2661,1556,1983]" pageId="248" pageNumber="526">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pearson" authorityYear="1958" box="[2070,2305,1674,1707]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Phyllotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="248" pageNumber="526" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="caprinus">Phyllotis caprinus</taxonomicName>
was originally allied to “P” 
<taxonomicName box="[2135,2264,1718,1747]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Tapecomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="248" pageNumber="526" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wolffsohni">wolffsohni</taxonomicName>
(now 
<taxonomicName box="[2368,2647,1718,1747]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Tapecomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="248" pageNumber="526" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="wolffsohni">Tapecomys wolffsohni</taxonomicName>
), an association that should be explored in more detail. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[2069,2657,1836,1865]" pageId="248" pageNumber="526" type="distribution">
<caption box="[2069,2657,1836,1865]" inLine="true" pageId="248" pageNumber="526" targetBox="[1455,2046,1563,1977]" targetPageId="248">
<paragraph blockId="248.[2068,2661,1556,1983]" box="[2069,2657,1836,1865]" pageId="248" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2069,2245,1836,1865]" pageId="248" pageNumber="526">Distribution.</emphasis>
S Bolivia and NW 
<taxonomicName box="[2509,2653,1836,1865]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Argentina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="248" pageNumber="526" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Argentina</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="248" pageNumber="526" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="248.[2068,2661,1556,1983]" pageId="248" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2069,2348,1871,1904]" pageId="248" pageNumber="526">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 102-140 mm, tail 116-151 mm, ear 23-26 mm, hindfoot 21-28 mm. No specific data are
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="248.[1455,2662,1989,2534]" pageId="248" pageNumber="526">
available for body weight. The Capricorn Leaf-eared Mouse is moderately large and relatively shortfurred, very similar to Yellow-rumped Leaf-eared Mouse (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Waterhouse" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[2404,2593,2028,2061]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Phyllotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="248" pageNumber="526" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="xanthopygus">P. xanthopygus</taxonomicName>
) but slightly larger in body size, with thickertail and typically buffy pectoral streak. The Capricorn Leaf-eared Mouse is characterized by flat, sharp-edged, long-waisted interorbital region and V-shaped coronal suture. Chromosomal complement is 2n = 38, FN = 72.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="248" pageNumber="526" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="248.[1455,2662,1989,2534]" pageId="248" pageNumber="526">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1457,1568,2186,2219]" pageId="248" pageNumber="526">Habitat.</emphasis>
Brushy habitats and stone walls in 
<taxonomicName box="[2070,2141,2186,2219]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Puna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="248" pageNumber="526" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Puna</taxonomicName>
environments at elevations of 2100-4500 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
